669
00:44:17,807 --> 00:44:22,517
These sharks and thousands
of hagfish stripped the carcass bare

670
00:44:22,607 --> 00:44:26,998
and this was all that was left
18 months later when we returned.

671
00:44:32,567 --> 00:44:36,037
Craig's main interest in returning
was to collect pieces of bone

672
00:44:36,327 --> 00:44:38,318
to take them to the surface.

673
00:44:38,407 --> 00:44:40,477
For Mike, it was another opportunity

674
00:44:40,567 --> 00:44:43,525
to film this eerie
but fascinating spectacle.

675
00:44:45,007 --> 00:44:47,475
<i>It's amazing, It's just evolved,</i>

676
00:44:47,567 --> 00:44:49,842
<i>When we first got down there,</i>

677
00:44:49,927 --> 00:44:52,316
<i>it looked like no meat, all skeleton,</i>

678
00:44:52,407 --> 00:44:54,602
<i>I thought, ''Ah, well, that's great, ''</i>

679
00:44:54,887 --> 00:44:58,766
<i>Big rib cages and hagfish</i>
